for other uses see open drive disambiguation open drive is a file search engine created by google in 2012 that enables the finding of files stored in the cloud that are publicly shared google refers to open drive as a collective encyclopedia project based on google drive public files and on the crowd sharing crowd sourcing and crowd solving principles 1 open drive will also return search results from other cloud storage content services including dropbox skydrive evernote and box open drive is available as a chrome app edit see also cloud computing peer to peer file sharing napster file hosting service edit references open drive on google 